### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "goldCardNumber": 55501,
    "name": "Elsa Milhet",
    "email": "milhet@juniata.edu",
    "password": "securePass123",
    "dateOfBirth": "2002-05-15",
    "phoneNumber": 123456789,
    "prefersMusic": "Rock",
    "prefersConversation": "Yes",
    "prefersPets": "Dogs only",
    "prefersSmoke": "No",
    "driverLicense": "PA-987654321"
}

### 2. Login
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "milhet@juniata.edu",
    "password": "securePass123"
}

### 3. Get User Profile (Replace :id with a real goldCardNumber)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/55501

### 4. Create a Ride 
POST {{baseUrl}}/rides
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "departureTime": "2:00:00",
    "date_": "2026-06-15",
    "destination": "Test",
    "availableSeats": 4,
    "price": 30,
    "goldCardNumber": 102
}

### 5. Get All Available Rides (Ta route actuelle)
GET {{baseUrl}}/rides

### 6. Filter Rides by Destination
GET {{baseUrl}}/rides?destination=Paris

### 7. Filter Rides by Date
GET {{baseUrl}}/rides?date=2026-04-01

### 8. Filter Rides by Destination AND Date
GET {{baseUrl}}/rides?destination=Paris&date=2024-06-15

### 9. Get Specific Ride Details (Success)
GET {{baseUrl}}/rides/RIDE-001
Accept: application/json

### 10. UPDATE a Ride (PUT)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/rides/RIDE-001
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "destination": "Lyon",
    "date_": "2026-07-15",
    "departureTime": "10:30:00",
    "price": 35,
    "availableSeats": 2,
    "goldCardNumber": 101
}

### 11. DELETE a Ride
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/rides/RIDE-004

### 12. Get all rides offered by a specific driver
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/102/rides
Accept: application/json

### 13. Get all comments and stars for a specific driver
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/55501/vehicle
Accept: application/json

### 14. Get all comments and stars for a specific driver
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/102/reviews
Accept: application/json

### Confirm or modify the booking status
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/bookings/BOOK-501
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "confirmed"
}
